cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper is about evolving synaptic plasticity rules to produce novel behaviors without reinforcement signals. This involves optimization of artificial neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves maze-navigation, which is a task related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a search heuristic to find the behavior that can solve the problem, which is related to optimization and control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method against a random search, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
